ial state while illuminating the efforts of Indigenous people to create lives of dignity and shared purpose in the face of turbulence, grief, and tightening governmental controls.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAboriginal AustraliansxUrban residence. 0aMigration, InternalzAustralia. 0aUrban Aboriginal Australians. 0aWarlpiri (Australian people)xSocial conditions. 0aWomen, Aboriginal AustralianxSocial conditions. 0aWomen, WarlpirixSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aSociety for Humanistic Anthropology Book Prizes.  aVictor Turner Prize.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022077?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022077423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022077/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DSLb2021